FBIS4-36194 "drnes109_l_94014" FBIS-NES-94-109 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 ISRAEL Poll Indicates Netanyahu Leads Likud Candidates Poll Indicates Netanyahu Leads Likud Candidates TA0306113894 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 3 Jun 94 p 7] TA0306113894 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT Hebrew BFN [Dahaf Institute Poll Conducted by Dr. Mina Tzemah] [Text] The following question was put to a representative sample of Likud members: Which of the following people do you consider best suited to be the Likud's candidate for prime minister in the next elections (answers given in percentage points)? Binyamin Netanyahu--48; Binyamin Begin--17; Ari'el Sharon--14; David Levi--9; Dan Meridor--8; none of the above--3; no reply--1. The poll was held on Tuesday and Wednesday among a representative sample of 503 Likud members. The maximum margin of error is 4 percent.
